tafsir[5]{c,v,t}:
  36,15,"They said) i.e. the apostles said: (Ye are but mortals) human beings (like unto us. The Beneficent hath naught revealed) He has not revealed any Scripture or sent any messenger. (Ye do but lie) about Allah!"
  36,17,"And our duty is but plain conveyance (of the message)) from Allah with a language that you all understand."
  36,20,"(And there came from the uttermost part of the city) there came from the centre of the city (a man) his name was Habib the carpenter (running) when he heard about the emissaries. (He cried: O my people! Follow those who have been sent) by accepting faith in Allah!"
  36,24,"(Then truly I should be in error manifest) if I worship anything besides Allah."
  36,26,"(It was said (unto him): Enter Paradise) Paradise was decreed for him; it is also said: it was said to his spirit: enter Paradise. (He said) his spirit said after entering Paradise: (Would that my people knew) and believed"